Privacy Policy
Flowy Privacy Policy
Effective date: April 19, 2026

Flowy (“we”, “us”, “our”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and share your information when you use Flowy.

1. Information we collect

We may collect the following information:

Email address

Name

Profile photo

Habit data you enter into the app, such as routines, streaks, goals, check-ins, notes, and progress information

Subscription status and purchase history

Device and usage data, such as app version, crash logs, and basic analytics

2. How we collect it

We collect information directly from you when you register, sign in, create habits, update your profile, or subscribe to a plan. We may also receive information from third-party providers such as Google Sign-In and payment processors.

3. How we use it

We use your information to:

Create and manage your account.

Show your profile and app content.

Store and sync your habit data.

Process subscriptions and lifetime purchases.

Send important service and account messages.

Improve app performance, reliability, and security.

4. Legal basis and consent

Where required by law, we process your personal data based on your consent, our contract with you, legitimate interests in operating and improving the app, and compliance with legal obligations.

5. Sharing of information

We do not sell your personal information. We may share data with trusted service providers that help us operate Flowy, such as authentication, hosting, analytics, and payment services, only to the extent necessary for those services. We may also disclose information if required by law.

6. Data retention

We keep your account and habit data while your account is active or as needed to provide the service. If you delete your account, we will remove or anonymize your personal data within a reasonable period, unless we must keep certain information for legal, security, or accounting reasons.

7. Your rights

Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or export your personal data, and to object to or restrict certain processing. You can contact us to exercise these rights.

8. Children’s privacy

Flowy is not intended for children under the age required by applicable law to consent to data processing. If we learn that we collected personal data from a child in violation of applicable rules, we will take steps to delete it.

9. Security

We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your information, but no method of transmission or storage is completely secure.

10. Third-party services

Flowy may use third-party services such as Google Sign-In, Firebase, analytics, or payment providers. Their own policies apply to information they process.

11. Changes to this policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the effective date and may notify you if the changes are significant.

12. Contact

For privacy requests or questions, contact: Andrea Ballarin — [andreaballarin94@gmail.com].
